<br>
I'm still trying to cobble together a decent suit of resist gear following our Naggy raid.  Two named Wurms in Burning Woods are rumored to occasionally drop this nice ALL/ALL shoulder item:<br>
<br>
Wurm Scale Coat   <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  <br>
AC: +8 Magic Resist: +10 Fire Resist: +20  <br>
Weight: 0.0 <br>
Classes: All Classes  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Shoulder<br>
 Required: Yes <br>
Can be stored in Medium and larger containers <br>
Last updated: Wed Aug 14 16:12:31 2002 <br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 <br>
Effect: Improved Damage II <br>
Type: Triggered <br>
Charges: Unlimited <br>
Level for Effect: 1 <br>
 <br>
<br>
The Wurms are Nezekezena and Phurzicon.  Their other drops include a Bard epic piece that drops everytime, a rare Mage Epic piece, and spells etc.  I haven't been able to find much out about the coat, other than it is more rare than it used to be when the zone was new. Most posts at Allakhazam are from 2000 or 2001.<br>
<br>
Nezekezena is 51 and gates, summons and has lots of HP.  Phurzicon is supposed to be quite a bit easier.<br>
<br>
Both Wurms and their PH's are wanderers but their spawn point, or points, are known.  The idea is to go to the spawn area and start killing everything you can in the area.  Eventually you or someone else will kill the current PH somewhere, and another will pop at the spawn point.  Once you get a spawn on the point you're set - you kill it where it stands, and another PH or Wurm pops 90 seconds later.<br>
<br>
PH's can be any mob in the zone, so every 90 seconds anything from light blue (lowest I've seen, maybe lower?) to white at 51 can pop.<br>
<br>
This is hands-down the best droppable resist piece for shoulder slot I've seen for a monk.  In fact, if I happen to win one it will be my full time shoulder slot.  I've never seen one in the stores (and yeah, I know what that prolly means..) so I'm asking for your help <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Any takers?  Anyone else interested in one?     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mjolner>Mjolner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/16/02 11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wurm Scale Cloak</span><hr size=1> I do not need one, but I would be more than glad to spend an evening or two helping you get one.<br>
